  "text": "We define a software operation summary as an overview providing knowledge of recent in-the-field software operation, based on acquired software operation information. The operation information needed for composition of the summary can be acquired by vendors from their software operating in the field, in a generic manner [CITATION_1] . Both the operation information on which an SOS is based, as well as the operation knowledge provided by the summary are related to the in-thefield performance, quality or usage of the software, or to the feedback of end-users of the software [CITATION_2] . An abstract SOS is provided in figure 1 .",
